As of the 2021 [[census]] estimates,<ref name="GR2" /> there were 2,682 people living in Bath, a decrease of 0.4% from 2010. There are 1,344 males (50.1%) and 1,338 females (49.9%). The [[population density]] was 2,947 people per square mile . There were 1,221 housing units at an average density of 1,357 per square mile. Racially, the borough consists of 79% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 6.6% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.3% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.5% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], and 8.2% from two or more races.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Explore Census Data |url=https://data.census.gov/table?q=bath+pa+populatoin&tid=DECENNIALPL2020.P1 |access-date=2023-04-07 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

The percentage of married families in Bath is 37.7%, cohabitating couples 18.7%, male householders without a partner 15.9%, and female householders without a partner 27.6%.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Explore Census Data |url=https://data.census.gov/table?q=bath+pa+household&tid=ACSDP5Y2021.DP02 |access-date=2023-04-07 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref> The number of people over the age of 25 with at least a high school diploma is 90.2%. Those with a bachelor's degree or higher is 18.9% and residents with a graduate or professional degree is 5.2%.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Explore Census Data |url=https://data.census.gov/table?q=bath+pa+education&tid=ACSST5Y2020.S1501 |access-date=2023-04-07 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref> The [[unemployment]] percentage in 2021 was 7%.<ref name="auto">{{Cite web |title=Explore Census Data |url=https://data.census.gov/table?q=bath+pa+dp03 |access-date=2023-04-07 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref> In 2020, the median income for a household in the borough was $53,250 and the [[per capita income]] for the borough was $23,233.

The average house or condo value was $170,900 and the average cost for rent was $1,189.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Explore Census Data |url=https://data.census.gov/table?q=bath+pa+dp04 |access-date=2023-04-07 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref> About 14% of families and 17.8% of the population were below the [[poverty line]].<ref name="auto"/>

